steps.instruction:
## Putting it all together

With the model updated, wire up the views and templates to make everything per-user.

In `todos/views.py`, update the three protected views:

```python
@login_required
def index(request):
    todos = Todo.objects.filter(user=request.user)
    return render(request, 'todos/index.html', {'todos': todos})

@login_required
def add_todo(request):
    if request.method == 'POST':
        text = request.POST.get('text', '').strip()
        if text:
            Todo.objects.create(text=text, user=request.user)
    return redirect('index')

@login_required
def delete_todo(request, todo_id):
    Todo.objects.filter(pk=todo_id, user=request.user).delete()
    return redirect('index')
```

In `todos/templates/todos/index.html`, add the username and a logout link:

```html
<p>Hello, {{ request.user.username }}! <a href="{% url 'logout' %}">Logout</a></p>
```

Run migrations after updating the model:
```
python manage.py makemigrations
python manage.py migrate
```

Then create a test user via the Django admin or with `python manage.py createsuperuser` and log in. Your todos will be private to each account.

Update `index` in `views.py` to filter todos by `request.user`.

